[start section id="20103"]

I had the pleasure to meet with Mrs. Weiss and her husband.  She was referred to us by Dr. Sullivan.
The patient is a delightful 75-year-old woman from Palmdale Otter, retired from the phone company, here for our advice regarding what to do after resection of colon cancer.  I reviewed the Sacred Heart Hospital records including Dr. Weber note, pathology report, and surgical report, and the note from Ohio, NP, who saw Mrs. Weiss in the hospital after surgery.
Briefly, she is otherwise a very healthy 75-year-old female who about four weeks ago underwent a laparoscopic right hemicolectomy for a T3, N1 colon cancer and has recovered from surgery without any complications.  She is up and about and asymptomatic and has for the most part an unremarkable past medical history.

[end section id="20103"]

